oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of an unidentified woman at the grave of Pvt. Frank M. Ring, Co. A, 114th MG Batn., 30th Div.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The Ring family of Franklin, Tennessee provided three of their four sons to World War I. The third oldest, Pvt. Frank M. Ring, Co. A, 114th MG Battn., 30th Div., was killed on October 9, 1918 and buried at the Somme American Cemetery. This photograph shows a lady placing flowers on the grave of Pvt. Frank Ring, Co. A, 114th MG Battn., 30th Div. She is also seen in [GWfran130]. She is believed to be a relation of a co-worker of Capt. Joesph Jasper Ring, 308th Engineeers at Allis-Chalmers Company.
